name: Pilates For Flexibility
vimeo_metadata_description: Lengthen, strengthen and elongate every muscle in your body with this workout that dramatically enhances you flexibility! These conditioning exercises articulate the spine and achieves optimal alignment. It will stretch out muscles and tendons such as the gluteals, hamstrings, back extensors and hip flexors, all of which can cause imbalances and injuries throughout the body when they are too tight. Stand taller, prouder and stronger than ever before with this multi-level, amazing workout!

name: Top Hip Stretches: How To Get Flexible Hips!
vimeo_metadata_description:
It’s so important to give the hips, and particularly the Psoas or the hip flexor muscles, the attention they so desperately need!

Regardless of whether you have an office job and you spend hours sitting at your desk, or you are extremely active with cycling, hiking, running etc. it is inevitable that your hip flexors will be tight without proper stretching.

It’s essential that we all focus on lengthening and stretching this area to prevent knee and hip injuries, to maintain the health of the hip joint and to ensure our pelvis is correctly aligned to avoid lower back pain. 

All you need for these exercises is your mat, so let’s get started!
vimeo_metadata_name: Top Hip Stretches: How To Get Flexible Hips!

name: Postnatal Stamina & Strength Leg Workout
vimeo_metadata_description: We will be working on the deep stabilising muscles that support the pelvis to improve endurance, support and strength. The benefits of this workout are incredible, as a new mum you will be experiencing things you may never have experienced before, such as back pain, hip pain and pelvic floor dysfunction. This workout will not only help eliminate aches and pains, but also help to improve muscle tone and strength of the pelvic floor by targeting the VMO muscle.

name: Internal Resistance Workout
vimeo_metadata_description:
The reason why Pilates is SO effective for toning and sculpting your body is internal resistance, creating an oppositional force by engaging deep stabilising muscles, to build strong, yet limber muscles.

The combination of eccentric and isometric contraction is what gives Pilates the edge.

This workout will challenge you to move with precision, flow and control by simply working against gravity and the resistance you create. You will learn the secret to continually getting more and more out of every single workout: turning up the resistance!

This small but mighty muscle is crucial for maintaining healthy hip and knee joints, ensuring the pelvis is correctly aligned and to fend off back aches and pains!

Repeat this entire series through three times on each side for a killer butt workout!

This is a sneak peek at our latest "Rehab Series: Knee Pain and Bursitis" full length routine from our Online Workout Studio https://pilatesbylisa.com.au.

Today we are focusing on rehabilitating knee pain, in particular the extremely common condition called "Bursitis". Knee bursitis is when the small sacs of fluid (known as the bursa) that act as lubrication between the bones, skin, muscles and tendons that surround it become inflamed and sore. This short and sweet routine will help to alleviate pain, correct knee alignment, stretch and strengthen all of the correct muscles so you can completely eliminate knee pain for good!

name: Pilates For Back Pain
vimeo_metadata_description: Banish back pain for good with this gentle, effective Pilates workout. This workout focuses on the underlying structural imbalances in the body that lead to joint pain and muscle tightness. The exercises are performed with meticulous attention to alignment, creating the perfect conditions for strengthening the muscles and allowing the body to move exactly how it should to achieve perfect posture. The beauty of this workout is that every exercise is adaptable to suit individual ability levels, so you can work at your own pace and slowly build the strength and flexibility you need to eliminate tightness, stiffness and soreness.

name: Face Dry Brushing Routine
vimeo_metadata_description:
Discover the incredible benefits of dry brushing for your face and neck with this simple yet effective daily routine! Dry brushing is a natural anti-aging beauty technique that helps to:
✔️ Boost circulation for a healthy, youthful glow
✔️ Promote lymphatic drainage to reduce puffiness & toxins
✔️ Gently exfoliate for smoother, clearer skin
✔️ Support collagen production to firm & plump fine lines
✔️ Enhance product absorption for maximum hydration & nourishment
✔️ Define facial contours & sculpt your jawline & cheekbones
✔️ Reduce fluid retention & awaken dull, tired skin

Incorporating this dry brushing technique into your morning or evening skincare routine will brighten, tighten, and tone your skin over time. This is the ultimate natural beauty hack to achieve glowing, youthful, sculpted skin—without invasive treatments or harsh chemicals!

name: Introduction To The Reformer: Short & Long Box
vimeo_metadata_description:
Today will be an overview of the traditional Short Box and Long Box exercises. The short box and long box are the same piece of apparatus, it's simply determined by which way the box is placed on the carriage! The options are endless with the box, so let's explore it's versatility!

The 1.2m wooden dowel I am using in this video was purchased at Bunnings, a hardware department store. These are useful in your Reformer practice however they are not essential, I try to keep the usage of props in our Reformer workouts to a minimum for convenience and ease of use for everyone.

description:
This amazing complete body stretching session is going to incorporate everything we've learned over the past six workouts throughout the program to make a comprehensive complete body routine! 

We will start in standing and perform amazing movements that stretch the spine, upper body and the entire posterior chain with flexion and rotation. We will then move down to the mat for further stretching of the hips, hamstrings, more upper body and quadriceps to ensure that you can see and feel just how far you have come!

description:
This travel vlog is a week in the life of my partner Tim and I as we film down in Australia's hidden gem, Tasmania!

Tim and I started filming our travels a couple of years ago when we were living in an RV, filming workout videos and travelling to every mainland state in the USA, and we've loved it ever since! We absolutely love looking back on our adventures, and I hope you enjoy them too!

We explore the best of what Tasmania has to offer, including cafes, restaurants, beaches, The Port Arthur Historic Site, Port Arthur Lavender Farm, Tasmania Unzoo, Tasman Arch, The Taste Of Tasmania Festival and more! I hope you enjoy! 

Get unlimited access to over 500 full length, real time workout videos from all over the globe: https://www.pilatesbylisa.com.au

description:
In today’s day and age we are constantly connected and caffeinated, so it's no wonder a good night's sleep seems near impossible!

This vlog has been inspired by my brother Michael and my boyfriend Tim. Both of the boys are bankers and have high stress jobs, they find it extremely difficult to not only switch off at the end of the day and de-stress, but also to get a good night steep. Their quest for a full night of rest lead us to discover some scientifically proven tips and techniques that truly worked for all of us, and I’m excited to share them with you today!

We've all experienced the stress, discomfort and anxiety of a sleepless night at one stage or another, but you CAN cure your insomnia naturally by making a few simple adjustments, make sure you implement these simple steps into your daily routine and you won't believe the difference!

name: Pilates For Dancers Reformer Workout
vimeo_metadata_description:
Dancers are INCREDIBLE athletes, however for longevity, safety, body awareness and preservation of the joints, tissue and muscles, Pilates is the ULTIMATE cross training addition! 

This workout is designed to improve a dancers (and dancers at heart!) understanding of core stability, weight placement and alignment. We will be focusing on the small, intrinsic muscles that protect the spine, pelvis, hip, knees and ankles. So if you’re a professional dancer or just want to create the long, lean lines of a ballerina, this workout is for you!

name: Plantar Fasciitis Tutorial
vimeo_metadata_description: Plantar fasciitis is a common and often persistent repetitive strain injury that can affect anyone, particularly runners, walkers and nearly anyone who stands fon their feet for long periods of time. It is a sharp pain in the bottom of your heel, it is often worse in the morning and causes pain when you walk on it. This tutorial will help alleviate and eliminate the symptoms by stretching the Plantar Fascia ligament, reducing inflammation and breaking up scar tissue.

name: My Pregnancy Transformation: Week By Week Progress!
vimeo_metadata_description:
My pregnancy Journey: a project almost a year in the making! �����

We started documenting this when I first found out I was pregnant, and I can’t believe the incredible journey it has been now Olivia is 12 days old! ��I’ve never felt happier, prouder, stronger or amazed by just what a woman’s body is capable of in my life! I’ve always had a great relationship with my body and my own mother always taught me to focus on being healthy over looking a certain way, but for me, and I’m sure many mum’s out there, body positivity has taken on a whole new meaning. �

The respect and gratefulness I have for a body that grew my beautiful daughter Olivia, looked after me throughout my pregnancy, did everything it could for a safe, natural delivery and now working away at healing and mending is just mind blowing. ���The post-partum journey is remarkable. Olivia and I have already been working together during tummy time on gentle postnatal stretching and strengthening routines that I can’t wait to share with you! ��‍♀️Every woman’s journey is different & every mum has her own unique path, but I think it’s important we all just adopt one thing: kindness towards our bodies. 

Everything you think and say to that body is important because it’s always listening, and so are those beautiful babies of ours! Tell yourself and  baby every day you are beautiful, capable, strong and incredible. You are exactly where you need to be.You can do anything you set that mind to. You are loved, always. �

name: Hamstring Release Tutorial
vimeo_metadata_description:
Tight, inflexible hamstrings are extremely common and can lead to chronic back, hip and knee pain. When we sit for extended periods of time with our knees bent and slouching, it causes the hamstrings to shorten and tighten (this position leads to tight hip flexors also).

This tutorial stretches and strengthens the hamstrings using active stretching techniques to reverse neuromuscular setting patterns to ensure you are flexible, strong and pain free.

vimeo_ott_metadata_description:
These are some of my all time favourite face exercises to tighten and lift the face!

I was introduced to these exercises by my 86 year old grandmother, and if you could see her you'd be doing these exercises every day too! She has a beautiful glow to her skin, it's absolutely flawless and smooth. She credits this all to her face exercise routine!

 Just like exercising other parts of your body, face exercises can help tone and strengthen the muscles in your face. Regular practice may lead to improved muscle tone, resulting in a firmer and more defined appearance.

They also increase blood circulation, reduce facial tension and stress, enhance facial symmetry, improve skin elasticity and best of all it is a 100% natural approach to beauty and wellbeing. 

This routine only takes 10 minutes per day, you can do it anytime, anywhere: watching TV, in the shower, waiting at the traffic lights or even standing in line at the supermarket (not for the faint hearted!)

Check out the entire routine and watch your face transform before your eyes!
vimeo_ott_metadata_tags: Complete Face Lifting Workout, face exercise, face exercises, face yoga, face workout

name: Postnatal Reformer Workout
vimeo_metadata_description: This is a routine that I personally developed and used throughout my recovery after the birth of my daughter Olivia. After getting the doctor's approval, I started using this class to regain my strength, stamina, muscle tone and flexibility. It has been my go to ever since! I'm now five months post partum and feel the happiest, healthiest and strongest I've ever felt! This is also a great routine to do if you are looking for a way to build up your strength and confidence with the reformer if you are returning from injury, just getting started or want a solid workout with simple, effective exercises!

description:
Whether you are expecting or not, this is an INCREDIBLE upper body routine for everybody! As our bellies continue to expand with baby, we tend to adopt a kyphotic posture with rounded shoulders to compensate for the extra weight we are carrying, throwing us completely out of alignment!

This workout is designed to counteract this, we are conditioning the core, opening up and strengthening the chest, stabilising the shoulders, and defining and lengthening the back so we have beautiful posture! I was just into my second trimester at the time of filming, but this is suitable for ALL trimesters! 

This is a sneak peek at our latest "Strength & Posture Prenatal" full-length routine, if you would love to try our full length, world-class workout videos, sign up for our FREE 10 day trial on our online studio!

name: Daily Dose Mat Program Introduction
vimeo_metadata_description:
Welcome to your Daily Dose Matwork Program! This program consists of five brand NEW 20-minute daily workouts, crafted first and foremost to be no-dread, feel good, effective routines. Each routine is a go-to solution for those days where motivation and energy might be low and you want workouts you can turn to no matter the mood.

Alongside the workouts, you’ll  receive a FREE challenge eBook where you will find daily goals that encourage you to integrate mindful practices and wellness habits into every part of your day. From nurturing morning rituals that set a positive tone, to nutrition tips that sustain your energy, and mindfulness exercises that clear your mind—each element is designed to enhance not only your physical fitness but also your mental and emotional health.

My hope is that these Pilates routines and the accompanying eBook empower you to take charge of your well-being, no matter how hectic your schedule may be. Let this challenge be your guide to a more balanced, healthier lifestyle, where taking care of yourself becomes a natural part of your day.

description:
This amazing core routine will help you achieve THE strongest abs and sleek, slim obliques! In this routine we are working on the Powerhouse which is comprised of all of the muscles around the waistline. No need for the gym, timetables or traffic when you can do all your workouts from home! These ab strengthening, core sculpting, oblique chiseling moves will achieve incredible results!

This Pilates core circuit is designed to strengthen, define and tone all the muscles in your core. Traditional mat pilates with a twist, these exercises work the entire Powerhouse.

QUICK TIPS:

Rock’n’Roll: Pull the abdominal wall to the spine and initiate the movement from the pelvis, tucking under to propel your roll back onto your shoulders. Don't roll too far back onto the neck or head.

Oblique Twist: A little twist on the half roll down. Keep your spine in a c-curve throughout and always reach the underneath arm for the corner of the mat. Extend the opposite leg without moving the pelvis.

Toe Taps: Ensure the pelvis stays in neutral, keep your navel drawn into the spine and maintain a 90 degree angle at the knee throughout.

Dead Bugs: Extend the same arm and leg down towards the ground at same time, whilst simultaneously extending the opposite arm above the head. Keep the spine neutral throughout.Try it right now! https://www.pilatesbylisa.com.au

name: Tutorial: How To Perfect The Leg Circle
vimeo_metadata_description: Tutorial: How To Perfect The Leg Circle! The leg circle is one of my favourite exercises. The main aim is pelvic stability, abdominal strength and control. When only one of our extremities is moving at any given time, it means that it is a “pure" stability exercise, the rest of our body is still and strong and only the limb is moving. This tutorial will perfect your leg circle and give you a deeper body awareness and understanding!

name: Ultimate Flexibility: Quadriceps
vimeo_metadata_description:
This workout routine focuses on stretching, lengthening and elongating the largest muscle group in the body, the quadriceps! We will be working our way from standing all the way down to the mat to stretch out every muscle from every possible angle!

Activities such as running, lifting heavy weights or jumping places excessive stress on the quadriceps. This ultimately leads to overuse of the quads and hip flexors during daily activities and also during exercise. If you've ever noticed the quads or hip flexors burning or tensing during certain exercises (for example, table top position) it means that they are too dominant and are taking all of the load that the hamstrings, core and glutes should be sharing too!

When quadricep muscles are overworked, they become tight and cause imbalance in the joints, particularly the knee. When tight quadriceps are accompanied by weak hamstrings, you have all the ingredients for an injury!

Too much sitting is another contributor to tight quads. When you sit at a desk for hours on end, your hip flexors shorten. Because all of the muscles connect to form a kinetic chain, tight hip flexors will also shorten the quads and cause them to be inflexible.

This workout routine is invaluable whether you are extremely active or have an office job to keep those legs long, lean, flexible and injury free!

description:
✅Arms ✅Butt ✅Core 
The ABC’s of an amazing PBL workout! 

Do you know my other ABC’s when it comes to our online workouts? ✅Athletic ✅Balanced ✅Clean: Athletic, challenging sequencing, balance and symmetry of the body and clean, precise, effective movement!❤️ 

Try this mini circuit for yourself! Perform 12 repetitions of each exercise for a total of three rounds, it covers the trifecta of fitness, cardio, strength and flexibility! 

Quick tips

1) 3-4 springs will keep the carriage stable whilst performing the sideovers, while the hip extensions and plyo pushups are most effective on one spring! 

2) Keep the extended arm beside the ear during sideovers to make sure the neck is staying aligned. 

3) Make a “tripod” with the supporting knee during hip extension, placing it directly in the centre for balance and control. 

4) Press the pelvis into the box and keep the spine neutral during plyo pushups, keep spring tension light as control trumps tension in this exercise!

For full length, real time, fully instructed reformer, matwork and apparatus Pilates classes that are the most effective blend of the classic method and contemporary moves, head to the online studio at www.pilatesbylisa.com.au. 

Explore the workouts, check out the programs, browse the weekly schedule and try our free 10 day trial!

name: Ultimate Flexibility Rotation
vimeo_metadata_download_links: [object Object], [object Object], [object Object], [object Object], [object Object], [object Object]
vimeo_metadata_thumbnails: [object Object], [object Object], [object Object], [object Object], [object Object], [object Object], [object Object]
vimeo_ott_metadata_description:
Pilates is so much more than abdominal exercises that involve heavy flexion of the spine. A well rounded Pilates workout incorporates flexion, extension, lateral flexion and rotation in order to create a healthy, flexible spine. Rotation is such a crucial aspect of the Pilates method as it strengthens the deep, intrinsic muscles that support the spine, creating the perfect marriage of strength and flexibility, which in turn creates even better flexion and extension. We can't have one without the other, and that’s why it’s so important that we concentrate on this often neglected plane of motion.
This workout is designed to improve our range of rotation. Practicing rotation feels incredible, you will see and feel the benefits right away! Improved rotation will allow you to achieve greater mobility not only in your Pilates practice, but also in day to day activites and sports that require rotation. This is an excellent workout for golfers, tennis players, footballers and swimmers!
vimeo_ott_metadata_tags: Ultimate Flexibility: Rotation, spine, healthy back, rotation, flexibility, stretch, pain, intrinsic, muscles, 10-20 minute matwork, 20-30 minute matwork, equipment free matwork, program, series, challenge

I've taken out all of the traditional, flexion-heavy core exercises and replaced them with fantastic alternatives so you can get an amazing core workout whilst still healing and strengthening your abdominals!
Suitable for all postnatal women who have been given approval to return to their exercise regime, including those with Diastasis Recti. A great workout for everyone, I have never had children and I still found this to really challenge my core!

vimeo_metadata_description: Ten minutes is all it takes to create a beautifully lean, defined midsection! name: Pilates For Surfing
vimeo_metadata_description: Dramatically improve your surfing technique with this fun, effective workout! Reduce your risk of injury in the surf by strengthening the deep core muscles that support your lower back, pelvis and hip joints. A strong powerhouse will provide you with greater strength, power and speed. Strength in your lower back, pelvis and hip joints is imperative to great surfing, allowing you to perform surfing turns with less effort. Enjoy this one before you hit the beach!

name: How to: Perfect Pilates Alignment
vimeo_metadata_description: A balanced, healthy spine is one that maintains its natural curves. Pilates encourages you to identify and achieve your optimal neutral spine. This tutorial will teach you how to attain your perfect alignment and also how to engage the “girdle of strength” in the center of your body, also known as your Powerhouse. Finally, you will learn how to incorporate Pilates breathing techniques to enhance your practice!

Online Pilates Workouts: https://www.pilatesbylisa.com.au

name: Prenatal PBL LIVE 43: Strong & Supple
vimeo_metadata_description: Today's workout is all about being and strong and supple throughout pregnancy! We are going to be doing a FANTASTIC workout that will strengthen, lengthen and tone the entire body. We will be working our core, every inch of lower body and finishing off with some incredible upper body sculpting moves! All you'll need is a pair of 0.5 kg (1lb) hand weights, no weights? No problem! A couple of cans of baked beans, tinned tomatoes, water bottles or anything else you have on hand are the perfect substitute!

description: This 25 minute workout video is designed to not only create the ultimate range of motion in your spine for incredible flexibility, but also relieve lower back pain, sciatica and eliminate aches and pains forever! The majority of back pain is caused by tightness and weakness in the stabilising muscles and mal-alignment of the pelvis and spine. These stretches not only help to realign and lengthen the spine and keep the pelvis in it's neutral position, but they also release tight muscles to eliminate pain for good!

description:
THE GLUTE BUILDER ⚡️⁣
Try my go-to glute workout, it's a great way to create muscle tone and strength and also work the deep stabilising muscles for hip and lower back health. ⁣
⁣
I love adding this workout into my routine, it's a great one to squeeze in when you want to feel WORKED in a short amount of time. (and Olivia loves when I get on the mat and do this routine with her too!)⁣
⁣
Try it right here, right now: ⁣
⁣
⚡️ Leg Lift - 15 reps⁣
⚡️ Hammy Curl - 15 reps ⁣
⚡️ Donkey Kick - 15 reps⁣
⚡️ Rotated Leg Lift - 15 reps⁣
⚡️ Rotated Hammy Curl - 15 reps⁣
⁣
Do 3 rounds on each side for a comprehensive, KILLER lower body workout. ⁣
⁣
If you're ready to try more full length, real time workouts, the PBL Online Studio is for you! With over 600 amazing workouts to suit all levels, including mat work, reformer, barre, yoga, programs, meditation and more! 
⁣

vimeo_ott_metadata_description:
Box breathing, also known as 4x4 breathing, involves inhaling to a count of four, holding your breath for a count of four, exhaling for four counts, and keeping the lungs empty for a count of four before repeating the same pattern.

4x4 breath will awaken mind/body awareness, create calm and release anxiety. Destress, reset and find solitude with every breath. This type of breathing has shown incredible results in supporting immune function, stress management and reducing blood pressure, leaving you feeling calm, happier and more present.
vimeo_ott_metadata_tags: Breathing Meditation Exercise, breath, breathing, meditation, anxiety, mindfulness, focus, breathe, box breathing, 4x4 breathing

name: Foam Roller Deep Tissue Release
vimeo_metadata_description:
We will be working deep into the muscles in this workout! Deep tissue massaging with the roller releases tightness, increases your range of motion and eliminates adhesions. 

An adhesion is a band of scar tissue that develops as the body attempts to repair itself. This can occur after surgery, infection, injury, trauma or radiation. Foam rolling will repair and eliminate these adhesions, giving you not only greater flexibility but also pain relief!

name: Total Babe Barre Workout
vimeo_metadata_description:
This barre workout video is an exceptional resource for both expectant mothers looking to maintain their fitness and well-being throughout pregnancy and anyone looking for an incredible cardio and toning routine. This workout offers a comprehensive workout that combines the grace of ballet, the flexibility of yoga, and the strength of pilates. This trifecta ensures a low-impact, total-body workout that focuses on enhancing muscular strength, improving balance, and increasing flexibility, all while being gentle on the joints and accommodating the changing pregnant body.

What sets this video apart is its adaptability for all fitness levels and stages of pregnancy. Each exercise is carefully curated to ensure safety and effectiveness, with modifications provided to cater to individual needs, making it an excellent choice for everyone from beginners to seasoned fitness enthusiasts. 

It incorporates exercises that target the pelvic floor, core, and other key muscle groups involved in labor and delivery. By promoting stamina, flexibility, and relaxation, this workout video not only aids physical preparation for childbirth but also contributes to mental well-being, making it a fantastic resource for expectant mothers seeking a holistic approach to prenatal fitness.

name: Ultimate Flexibility: Splits Routine
vimeo_metadata_description:
Aside from being an incredibly rewarding challenge, learning how to do the splits can benefit your health and fitness immensely! Having complete range of motion at the hip joint, strength in the stabilising muscles and incredibly flexible hamstrings, quadriceps and hip flexors is not only crucial to be able to perform the splits, but also a wonderful result of performing this workout routine! 

By practicing this Splits session regularly, not only will you be able to achieve the goal of getting into the splits position, but also dramatically improve your overall flexibility and your ability to execute all other Pilates moves with complete range of motion and perfect technique!

description:
Pilates is so much more than abdominal exercises that involve heavy flexion of the spine. A well rounded Pilates workout incorporates flexion, extension, lateral flexion and rotation in order to create a healthy, flexible spine. Rotation is such a crucial aspect of the Pilates method as it strengthens the deep, intrinsic muscles that support the spine, creating the perfect marriage of strength and flexibility, which in turn creates even better flexion and extension. We can't have one without the other, and that’s why it’s so important that we concentrate on this often neglected plane of motion.

This workout is designed to improve our range of rotation. Practicing rotation feels incredible, you will see and feel the benefits right away! Improved rotation will allow you to achieve greater mobility not only in your Pilates practice, but also in day to day activites and sports that require rotation. This is an excellent workout for golfers, tennis players, footballers and swimmers!

name: Ski Fit Circuit
vimeo_metadata_description: We filmed this workout at Green Lake in beautiful Whistler, British Columbia. This town is famous for it's Winter sports so it was appropriate to film an athletic conditioning circuit routine! For skiing and snowboarding you need strength, endurance and stamina in your stabilising muscles such as the gluteus medius and the internal and external oblique muscles. We are going to be working on all of these deep underlying muscles, making it the perfect workout no matter what sport you do! Even if you're not into sports, this workout will cinch your waist, tone your arms and define your lower body, giving you a Pilates figure!

These are the perfect exercises to engage those muscles, improve posture and strengthen the entire body including your powerhouse!

name: Ultimate Flexibility: Hip Stretch
vimeo_metadata_description:
It’s so important to give the hips and particularly the Psoas (the hip flexor muscle) the attention they so desperately need!

Regardless of whether you have an office job and you spend hours sitting at your desk, or you are extremely active with cycling, hiking, running etc. it is inevitable that your hips will be tight without proper stretching.

It’s essential that we all focus on lengthening and stretching this area to prevent knee and hip injuries, to maintain the health of the hip joint and to ensure our pelvis is correctly aligned to avoid lower back pain.

This workout stretches the hips through every possible range of motion including flexion, extension and rotation to ensure your hip joint is as fluid and flexible as possible!

All you need for these exercises is your mat, so let’s get started!

name: Facial Massage And Lymphatic Drainage Routine
vimeo_metadata_description:
This is THE Holy Grail of skincare!

Today I’m sharing with you something that isn’t only an integral part of my beauty regime, but it’s also central to my relaxation routine.

It helps me to unwind and de-stress at the end of every single day and also keeps wrinkles at bay! What is it? Facial and lymphatic drainage massage!

Stress, fatigue and sleep deprivation can show in your face through expression lines, puffiness and dullness. Facial massage decreases puffiness, improves circulation, decreases tension in the muscles that cause wrinkles and gives you a refreshed, healthy glow! 

This is an ancient Chinese practice that increases “chi” in certain areas. Keep watching to find out exactly how I massage my face with the Jade Roller!
vimeo_metadata_name: Facial Massage And Lymphatic Drainage Routine

name: The Rehab Series: Wrist Pain Tutorial
vimeo_metadata_description:
I designed this session with two main conditions in mind: Carpal Tunnel Syndrome and Tendonitis. 

Carpal Tunnel Syndrome occurs when the Median Nerve becomes suppressed or impinged within the "Carpal Tunnel". The Median Nerve is a nerve that originates at the spine, runs all the way down the inner arm and through the "Carpal Tunnel" in the wrist to give you feeling in the thumb, index finger, middle finger and the inside of the ring finger. 

The Carpal Tunnel is a passage way that is formed by bones and ligaments that allows the median nerve and tendons to run through, when the tendons become thickened or there is any impingement on the Median Nerve, this will cause the syndrome. 

Symptoms of Carpal Tunnel can be tingling, numbness and pain in the hand and can progress to the point where surgery is required. The condition can be caused by repetitive actions such as sitting at a computer and typing or using a mouse and also during pregnancy water retention can impinge on the nerve. 

Tendonitis is a general term for any time that the tendons become inflamed, and the same exercises in this tutorial will alleviate symptoms and eliminate pain for both conditions by strengthening, releasing and relieving.
vimeo_metadata_name: The Rehab Series: Wrist Pain Tutorial

name: Patellofemoral Syndrome (Knee Pain) Tutorial
vimeo_metadata_description:
Patellofemoral Syndrome is the most common of all kinds of knee pain, causing pain around and under your kneecap. It is extremely common and can affect anybody, from runners, cyclists and hikers to office workers and those who are less active in their jobs.
This tutorial will correct muscle imbalances, stretching and strengthening the muscles that support and stabilise the knee joint to ensure optimal tracking of the patella (kneecap). Get back on track and eliminate your pain with this class!

vimeo_metadata_description: This is an amazing pre-natal leg workout that will keep your legs lean strong and toned throughout your entire pregnancy! Suitable for all trimesters, you will feel strong and energised with this challenging yet gentle workout. The glutes play a critical role in maintaining correct posture during pregnancy as your centre of gravity changes and also during the labor process. This class will also dramatically  ease any discomfort in your back and hips, improve  your balance and enhance your stability. Take the class at your own pace and rest whenever you need to. You can gradually increase intensity and the number of repetitions as you improve your strength and endurance!

name: Athletic Performance Workout
vimeo_metadata_description:
Playing sports often comes hand in hand with muscle imbalances because of sport specific training. This means that some muscles become over developed, tight and inflexible whilst other muscles become weak and deficient. This can lead to injury, an athletes worst nightmare.

Pilates strengthens these stabilising muscles and provides athletes with the core strength, endurance and flexibility they require to perform at their peak. With this workout, you will dramatically improve your balance and control, increase blood flow to the internal muscles that support your spine and also acquire precision, coordination and power. All of the exercises are challenging, fun and functional.

name: Pilates For Sports
vimeo_metadata_description:
Agility, strength, stamina, flexibility and control are critical elements of sporting performance and prevention of injury. This workout is designed to enhance your sporting potential and improve your game. Whether it is an individual pursuit such as surfing, swimming or cycling, or a team sport such as rugby or soccer, then this is the ultimate core workout for you!

You will be strengthening crucial stabilising muscles that support the scapula and spine, protecting your joints and extending your sporting career. Join guest demonstrator Dane Muller and I for a fantastic workout and guaranteed results. I hope you love it as much as I do!

description:
May Makeover Challenge

FREE to all members!
Want to achieve your mid year goals? Need guidance on what to eat, when to workout or how to boost your motivation?  Then join us for our all new May Makeover Challenge which is shaping up to be our biggest and best yet. 

The May Makeover Challenge commences on Monday the 30th. April, is FREE for all members, and runs right through the month of May. It’s the perfect way to stay on track and reach your mid year goals. 

We’ve filmed all new workouts especially for this Challenge including an upper body shaping and sculpting routine, a powerhouse workout that’s designed to completely redefine your core, a lower body workout that will trim and sculpt through the legs and a complete body routine that will really tone, strengthen and lengthen the entire body. 

All members will receive the new Pilates by Lisa eBook which will introduce you to goal setting tools, bonus moves of the week, a full month workout schedule, delicious recipes with a new seven day meal plan, motivational tips, articles from our special guest writers, fantastic sponsor prizes and so much more!

 This challenge is designed to not only get you ready to reveal a brand new you, but also keep the results coming throughout the rest of the year! 

Make 2018 your biggest and best year yet. Plan for success and fall in love with how you look AND feel. 

Sign up and get started with me today. I can’t wait to workout with you!

name: Booster Complete Body
vimeo_metadata_description:
This 30-minute workout routine is a complete full-body session that seamlessly integrates targeted exercises for the core, upper body, lower body, and spinal mobility. Using minimal equipment—a booty band and a chair—this routine is designed to tone muscles, improve stability, and enhance flexibility, making it perfect for a balanced and efficient workout.

Workout Structure:
5-Minute Upper Body Booty Band Workout
Move on to your upper body with a booty band routine that targets the arms, shoulders, and back. The resistance from the band adds intensity, helping to build lean muscle and endurance.

5-Minute Standing Ab Workout
This segment focuses on strengthening and toning your entire midsection, improving posture and stability.

5-Minute Knee and Lower Body Strength with Chair and Booty Band
Next, focus on lower body strength, emphasising knee stability. Using a chair for support and a booty band for resistance, this segment strengthens the quads, hamstrings, glutes, and calves, improving overall lower body functionality.

5-Minute Lower Body Focus
Continue the lower body work with exercises specifically designed to lift and tone the glutes and inner thighs. Glute bridges and inner thigh lifts provide a concentrated burn for a sculpted lower body.

5-Minute Spinal Mobility Workout
Transition into a gentle spinal mobility segment to improve flexibility and relieve tension. This part of the routine helps maintain a healthy spine and enhances overall mobility, ensuring your body feels balanced and aligned.

name: Anti Aging Facial Pilates!
vimeo_metadata_description:
I was introduced to these exercises by my 80 year old grandmother, and if you could see her you'd be doing these exercises every day too! She has a beautiful glow to her skin, it's absolutely flawless and smooth. She credits this all to her facial exercise routine!

Your facial muscles play a critical role in the contouring and shaping of your face. These exercises increase circulation, improving the blood flow to your face to give you a healthy glow.

They also work the muscles that lie underneath the skin to not only assist with firming, lifting and toning the face, but also decreasing the tension that causes fine lines.

This routine only takes 10 minutes per day, you can do it anytime, anywhere: watching TV, in the shower, waiting at the traffic lights or even standing in line at the supermarket (not for the faint hearted!) Watch your face transform before your eyes!

description:
Our pelvic floor isn’t something we often think about when it comes to exercising, however keeping these muscles strong is crucial for women of all ages. These muscles are extremely important as they support your internal organs and help you control the bladder and bowel, so It is vital to keep your pelvic floor muscles strong!

This video will help you understand the function of the pelvic floor and the issues that can arise when the muscles are weak and not functioning correctly in this area and why it’s essential for all women to start Pelvic Floor exercises as soon as possible!

name: Pelvic Floor, Incontinence And Prolapse Rehabilitation Tutorial
vimeo_metadata_description:
Strengthening the pelvic floor can be difficult and challenging in a number of ways. It can be difficult to get motivated to perform the exercises or even know exactly how to do them.

This tutorial will give you the guidance, support and motivation you need to restore and maintain your optimal pelvic floor strength

Ideally, perform this tutorial several times per week and you will see incredible results.

This tutorial is not only beneficial for strengthening the pelvic floor, but also preventing and rehabilitating prolapse or incontinence. If you find that you have leakage when you cough, sneeze or exercise, this tutorial is the ultimate solution for you.

vimeo_metadata_description:
If you want a lean, sculpted, toned upper body, then this is the ultimate workout for you!  Not only will you reshape your body, but you will also strengthen crucial stabilising muscles that support the scapula and spine. You will correct your posture whilst standing taller and prouder than ever before!

I personally swear by this workout to define my upper body. Join me for a 20 minute exciting, challenging session that is guaranteed to get you results!
All you need is a mat, resistance band, towel and a drink of water! Thank you for watching, you are about to change your body and your life!

name: Jawline Sculpting Face Workout
vimeo_metadata_description:
Welcome to our 10-minute anti-aging jawline sculpting face exercise routine designed to give you a non-surgical face lift and help you achieve a sharper, more defined jawline! In this video, we’ll guide you through a series of effective face exercises that target the double chin, firm the jawline and neck, and provide a natural face lift. These exercises are perfect for anyone looking to tighten and tone their neck, sculpt their jaw and enhance their facial contours.

Benefits of this routine:
* Reduce double chin and lift and tone the neck area
* Sculpt and define your jawline
* Firm and lift sagging skin
* Improve skin elasticity and circulation
* Achieve a youthful, glowing appearance

name: Booster Spine Mobility
vimeo_metadata_description:
This 5-minute spinal mobility workout is designed to increase flexibility and relieve tension in your back with simple, effective movements that require no equipment. Perfect for those looking to improve their posture, reduce stiffness, or simply add a gentle stretch to their day, this routine focuses on moving the spine through its full range of motion. Each exercise promotes better spinal health, enhancing your ability to move comfortably and freely in daily life.

Incorporate this workout into your daily routine to maintain a healthy spine, improve your posture, and enjoy greater ease of movement. This quick session is ideal for anyone needing a gentle yet effective way to keep their back feeling its best.

description:
Here is a sneak peek at my Anti Aging Facial Pilates Routine!

I was introduced to these exercises by my 80 year old grandmother, and if you could see her you'd be doing these exercises every day too! She has a beautiful glow to her skin, it's absolutely flawless and smooth. She credits this all to her facial exercise routine!

Your facial muscles play a critical role in the contouring and shaping of your face. These exercises increase circulation, improving the blood flow to your face to give you a healthy glow.

They also work the muscles that lie underneath the skin to not only assist with firming, lifting and toning the face, but also decreasing the tension that causes fine lines.

This routine only takes 10 minutes per day, you can do it anytime, anywhere: watching TV, in the shower, waiting at the traffic lights or even standing in line at the supermarket (not for the faint hearted!)

Check out the entire routine at the link above and watch your face transform before your eyes!
name: Face Exercises: Non Surgical Facelift To Tighten Jawline, Firm Cheeks and Erase Lines!
vimeo_metadata_description:
Here is a sneak peek at my Anti Aging Facial Pilates Routine!

I was introduced to these exercises by my 80 year old grandmother, and if you could see her you'd be doing these exercises every day too! She has a beautiful glow to her skin, it's absolutely flawless and smooth. She credits this all to her facial exercise routine!

Your facial muscles play a critical role in the contouring and shaping of your face. These exercises increase circulation, improving the blood flow to your face to give you a healthy glow.

They also work the muscles that lie underneath the skin to not only assist with firming, lifting and toning the face, but also decreasing the tension that causes fine lines.

This routine only takes 10 minutes per day, you can do it anytime, anywhere: watching TV, in the shower, waiting at the traffic lights or even standing in line at the supermarket (not for the faint hearted!)

Check out the entire routine at the link above and watch your face transform before your eyes!
vimeo_metadata_name: Face Exercises: Non Surgical Facelift To Tighten Jawline, Firm Cheeks and Erase Lines!

description:
8 weeks post-partum and feeling happier and healthier than ever before! Try this quick workout with our fabric resistance band and follow along with me! ⁣
⁣
One of my missions with the PBL Online Studio is to empower, support and encourage women from all walks of life. 
⁣
So today I want to remind you that starting a family and having a baby doesn’t mean your career/body/life is over...it is only just the beginning! 
⁣
We CAN do it all, since Olivia arrived I feel like I have a much more profound respect and understanding of my own body and other women, both in a physical and mental sense. It has enriched the way I conduct my business and I it has added a completely new layer of technique and effectiveness to my workouts! I’ve also gained a whole new appreciation for the online studio fitting into my new, crazy, unpredictable schedule! 
⁣
I’ve learned that I can do anything I set my mind to, that our bodies are miraculous and that life has only just begun! 
⁣
If you’d like more of where this came from, try our latest “Band Burner” workout video on the online studio, you can also purchase our fabric resistance band on the online shop! https://www.pilatesbylisa.com.au

name: Prenatal Yoga Program Introduction
vimeo_metadata_description:
If you're looking for the perfect routine to stay fit, reduce pain and prepare for birth, this program is the ultimate.

⁣Consisting of six full-length, real time flows suitable for all stages of pregnancy, these incredible sequences will boost energy, balance hormones, strengthen the body and mind and improve tone and pelvic stability.

Each of the six videos has a different focus to suit every need, from bedtime relaxation to a morning energiser, hip and heart opening and lower body love, we definitely have you covered. These sessions are ideal to create balance, flexibility, and space in the body whilst providing self-care.

With complete Yoga and Pilates qualifications, you are in safe hands with options for all levels, it’s never too late to start!

name: Mum To Be Complete Body Workout
vimeo_metadata_description:
This Complete Body Reformer Workout, designed specifically with mums-to-be in mind, offers an inclusive and comprehensive exercise regimen that caters to the unique needs of pregnant women, while also being suitable for EVERY body! Filmed while I was 22 weeks into my own pregnancy, this workout serves as a testament to its safety, adaptability, and effectiveness during this special time.
The program is structured to provide a full-body workout that combines strength, flexibility, and balance exercises, ensuring participants can maintain fitness in a way that supports their needs. Special attention is given to core stability, pelvic floor strength, and overall body alignment, which are crucial areas for expectant mothers. Modifications and adjustments are thoroughly explained, allowing individuals at different stages of pregnancy or fitness levels to participate comfortably and safely.
This workout not only aims to help women stay active and healthy during pregnancy but also to prepare the body for childbirth and recovery postpartum. It emphasises gentle, controlled movements facilitated by the reformer. Whether you're an expectant mother, postnatal, or simply someone looking for a safe, effective way to stay fit, this Reformer Complete Body Workout is a versatile choice that promotes well-being, strength, and balance for all.

description: Diastasis Recti is a common condition that can occur during pregnancy when the connective tissue between the muscles of the abdominal wall tears to accommodate the baby. If the connective tissue does not naturally fuse again, it can leave you with a opening in the abdominal wall after the birth. Diastasis Recti can be simply fixed with targeted Pilates exercises that rehabilitate and strengthen the abdominals. This is an in depth tutorial that will guide you through how to establish if you have Diastasis Recti and healing exercises that will not aggravate or worsen the tear.

name: Gua Sha Routine
vimeo_metadata_description:
Welcome to The Pilates By Lisa Ultimate Gua Sha Massage Routine tutorial, where I’ll walk you through an easy, step-by-step Gua Sha follow-along routine designed for beginners and anyone looking to incorporate this powerful technique into their skincare routine. Whether you're a seasoned pro or just starting out, this facial Gua Sha tutorial will help you enhance your beauty and wellness regimen.

Gua Sha is a popular tool used in Chinese medicine, known for its ability to improve circulation, reduce puffiness, smooth fine lines, and promote healthy, glowing skin. In this video, I'll demonstrate how to perform a quick Gua Sha massage that can be done at home using a Gua Sha stone. This easy Gua Sha routine is perfect for both anti-aging benefits and relaxation, offering you a natural, holistic way to rejuvenate your skin.

What to expect in this video:


A simple and easy Gua Sha follow-along routine suitable for beginners.
Facial Gua Sha techniques to help tone and lift your face.
The anti-aging benefits of Gua Sha and its ability to reduce fine lines and wrinkles.
Gua Sha tips that promote lymphatic drainage, detoxification, and skin healing.
Learn how to use Gua Sha tools to improve circulation, reduce facial tension, and enhance your natural beauty.


This Gua Sha facial massage routine is the perfect addition to your skincare journey. Whether you're looking to enhance your anti-aging skincare routine or discover a relaxing new way to care for your skin, this video covers all the essentials!
